; Regression test for issue #1789: unbalanced transaction when using `format`
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1789
;
; The commodity `format` directive should affect only display formatting,
; never balance checking or the math used to infer implicit conversion
; prices.  Before the fix, parsing a journal that declared a display
; precision of 2 for commodity B and then used a smaller amount like
; `-0.001 B` in a two-commodity transaction produced:
;
;     While balancing transaction ...
;     Unbalanced remainder is: 1 A
;     Error: Transaction does not balance
;
; Root cause: xact_base_t::finalize() inferred a conversion price when the
; balance had exactly two commodities, but the check `if (*x && *y)`
; invoked `amount_t::operator bool()` == `!is_zero()`, which respects the
; commodity's display precision.  With `format 1000.00 B` (precision 2)
; the amount -0.001 B rounded to zero for display, so the guard skipped
; the conversion and left 1 A unbalanced.
;
; The related guard inside `amount_t::operator/=` had the same defect:
; dividing by an amount whose exact value is non-zero but rounds to zero
; at display precision wrongly threw "Divide by zero".  Both checks now
; use is_realzero(), which inspects the underlying rational value.
commodity B
    format 1000.00 B

2000/01/01 note
    Account    -0.001 B
    Account         1 A

test bal
                 1 A  Account
end test

test reg
00-Jan-01 note                  Account                         1 A          1 A
end test
